headline: Lockheed Martin to Quadruple Sales of Missile-Defense System to Pentagon
summary: The Pentagon entered a deal with Lockheed Martin to quadruple production of interceptors used to protect U.S. military bases and allies overseas.  Lockheed will increase Thaad interceptor production over seven years from 96 to 400 per year under the framework agreement with the Pentagon, the company said Thursday.  Thaad, or Terminal High Altitude Area Defense, systems can intercept ballistic missiles outside of the Earth’s atmosphere.
